Here are the user stories derived from the Python code:

1. As a Data Processor, I want to process deletions for a specific date, so that I can maintain clean and up-to-date records.  
2. As a UI Designer, I want to redesign the Resources page, so that it matches the new Broker styles.  
3. As a UI Designer, I want to report user testing results to agencies, so that they can provide feedback and improvements.  
4. As a DevOps Engineer, I want to configure New Relic for all applications, so that I can monitor performance and troubleshoot issues.  
5. As a Broker User, I want to sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load, so that data consistency is maintained.  
6. As a Broker Team Member, I want to update SQL codes for clarity, so that queries are easier to understand and maintain.  
7. As a Broker Team Member, I want to add 00***** and 00FORGN PPoPCode cases, so that special cases are properly handled.  
8. As a Broker Team Member, I want to derive FundingAgencyCode, so that data quality is improved.  
9. As an Agency User, I want to map FederalActionObligation to Atom Feed, so that financial data is accurately represented.  
10. As an Agency User, I want to validate PPoPZIP+4, so that it matches Legal Entity ZIP standards.  
11. As a Developer, I want to improve logging for troubleshooting, so that issues can be diagnosed faster.  
12. As a Developer, I want to ensure domain models are indexed, so that validation is faster.  
13. As a Website User, I want to access published FABS files, so that I can download and analyze data.  
14. As an Owner, I want to set up user testing based on SME input, so that feedback is incorporated early.  
15. As an Owner, I want to reset the environment to staging permissions, so that testing remains consistent.  
16. As a FABS User, I want to request read-only access to DABS, so that I can review submission data.  
17. As a FABS Developer, I want to update FABS submission status, so that workflows are correctly tracked.  
18. As a FABS Developer, I want to load GTAS window data to the database, so that financial reporting is accurate.  
19. As a FABS Developer, I want to deactivate the publish button during derivations, so that premature submissions are prevented.  
20. As a Historical Data Loader, I want to include FREC derivations in historical data, so that records are complete.  
21. As a Validation Manager, I want to update validation rules, so that they align with business requirements.  
22. As a Validation Manager, I want to prevent duplicate transactions from being published, so that data integrity is maintained.  
23. As a File Manager, I want to cache D File generation requests, so that repeated processing is minimized.  
24. As a File Manager, I want to prevent double publishing FABS submissions, so that data consistency is ensured.  
25. As an Agency Data User, I want to validate FABS rules for loan/non-loan records, so that compliance is enforced.  
26. As an Agency Data User, I want to ensure SAM data is complete, so that records are accurate and reliable.  
27. As a Cross-Cluster Team Member, I want to derive office names from codes, so that display names are user-friendly.  
28. As a Cross-Cluster Team Member, I want to update the sample file link to point to the correct file, so that users download the latest version.  
29. As a Cross-Cluster Team Member, I want to handle ZIP codes missing last 4 digits, so that partial entries are processed correctly.  
30. As a Cross-Cluster Team Member, I want to update status labels for the Submission Dashboard, so that progress is clearly communicated.

import logging
from datetime import date
from typing import List, Dict, Optional
from dataclasses import dataclass

# Configure logging
logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format='%(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s')
logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)

# Data Processing
class DataProcessor:
    def process_deletions_for_date(self, deletion_date: date) -> bool:
        """Process deletions for a specific date."""
        logger.info(f"Processing deletions for date: {deletion_date}")
        # Simulate deletion logic
        return True

# UI Design
class UIDesigner:
    def redesign_resources_page(self) -> str:
        """Redesign the Resources page to match new Broker styles."""
        return "Resources page redesigned with Broker styles."

    def report_user_testing_results(self, agencies: List[str], results: Dict) -> bool:
        """Report user testing results to agencies."""
        for agency in agencies:
            logger.info(f"Reporting test results to {agency}: {results}")
        return True

# DevOps
class DevOpsEngineer:
    def configure_new_relic(self, apps: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Configure New Relic for all applications."""
        for app in apps:
            logger.info(f"New Relic configured for {app}")
        return True

# Broker Functionality
class BrokerUser:
    def sync_d1_with_fpds(self) -> bool:
        """Sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load."""
        logger.info("D1 file generation synced with FPDS data load.")
        return True

class BrokerTeamMember:
    def update_sql_codes(self, sql_files: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Update SQL codes for clarity."""
        for file in sql_files:
            logger.info(f"Updated SQL code in {file}")
        return True

    def add_special_ppop_cases(self, cases: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Add special PPoPCode cases."""
        for case in cases:
            logger.info(f"Added special PPoP case: {case}")
        return True

    def derive_funding_agency_code(self) -> str:
        """Derive FundingAgencyCode."""
        derived_code = "DERIVED_AGENCY_CODE"
        logger.info(f"Derived FundingAgencyCode: {derived_code}")
        return derived_code

# Developer Tools
class Developer:
    def improve_logging(self) -> bool:
        """Improve logging for troubleshooting."""
        logger.info("Logging improved for better diagnostics.")
        return True

    def index_domain_models(self, models: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Ensure domain models are indexed for faster validation."""
        for model in models:
            logger.info(f"Indexed domain model: {model}")
        return True

# FABS Functionality
class FABSUser:
    def access_published_files(self) -> List[str]:
        """Access published FABS files."""
        files = ["file1.csv", "file2.csv"]
        logger.info(f"Accessed published FABS files: {files}")
        return files

    def request_dabs_access(self) -> bool:
        """Request read-only access to DABS."""
        logger.info("Requested read-only access to DABS.")
        return True

class FABSDeveloper:
    def update_submission_status(self, submission_id: str, status: str) -> bool:
        """Update FABS submission status."""
        logger.info(f"Updated submission {submission_id} to status: {status}")
        return True

    def load_gtas_data(self, data: Dict) -> bool:
        """Load GTAS window data to the database."""
        logger.info("GTAS window data loaded to database.")
        return True

    def deactivate_publish_button(self) -> bool:
        """Deactivate the publish button during derivations."""
        logger.info("Publish button deactivated during derivations.")
        return True

# Historical Data
class HistoricalDataLoader:
    def include_frec_in_historical_data(self) -> bool:
        """Include FREC derivations in historical data."""
        logger.info("FREC derivations included in historical data.")
        return True

# Validation
class ValidationManager:
    def update_validation_rules(self, rules: Dict) -> bool:
        """Update validation rules."""
        logger.info(f"Updated validation rules: {rules}")
        return True

    def prevent_duplicate_transactions(self) -> bool:
        """Prevent duplicate transactions from being published."""
        logger.info("Duplicate transactions prevented from publishing.")
        return True

# File Management
class FileManager:
    def cache_d_file_requests(self) -> bool:
        """Cache D File generation requests."""
        logger.info("D File generation requests cached.")
        return True

    def prevent_double_publishing(self) -> bool:
        """Prevent double publishing FABS submissions."""
        logger.info("Double publishing of FABS submissions prevented.")
        return True

# Cross-Cluster Team
class CrossClusterTeam:
    def derive_office_names(self, codes: List[str]) -> Dict[str, str]:
        """Derive office names from codes."""
        office_names = {code: f"Office_{code}" for code in codes}
        logger.info(f"Derived office names: {office_names}")
        return office_names

    def update_sample_file_link(self, new_link: str) -> bool:
        """Update the sample file link."""
        logger.info(f"Sample file link updated to: {new_link}")
        return True

    def handle_partial_zip_codes(self, zip_codes: List[str]) -> List[str]:
        """Handle ZIP codes missing last 4 digits."""
        processed_zips = [f"{z}0000" if len(z) < 5 else z for z in zip_codes]
        logger.info(f"Processed ZIP codes: {processed_zips}")
        return processed_zips

    def update_status_labels(self, labels: Dict[str, str]) -> bool:
        """Update status labels for the Submission Dashboard."""
        logger.info(f"Updated status labels: {labels}")
        return True

# Example Usage
if __name__ == "__main__":
    # Initialize classes
    data_processor = DataProcessor()
    ui_designer = UIDesigner()
    devops = DevOpsEngineer()
    broker_user = BrokerUser()
    broker_team = BrokerTeamMember()
    developer = Developer()
    fabs_user = FABSUser()
    fabs_dev = FABSDeveloper()
    historical_loader = HistoricalDataLoader()
    validation_mgr = ValidationManager()
    file_mgr = FileManager()
    cross_cluster = CrossClusterTeam()

    # Execute sample operations
    data_processor.process_deletions_for_date(date.today())
    ui_designer.redesign_resources_page()
    devops.configure_new_relic(["app1", "app2"])
    broker_user.sync_d1_with_fpds()
    broker_team.add_special_ppop_cases(["00*****", "00FORGN"])
    fabs_dev.load_gtas_data({"data": "sample"})
    cross_cluster.derive_office_names(["001", "002"])
